  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for sqlite3",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for sqlite3 fixes the following issues\n\nUpdate to 3.53.2:\n\n- CVE-2026-11822: memory corruption vulnerabilities in the FTS5 full-text search extension that allow attackers to cause\n  process crashes, memory exhaustion, or arbitrary code execution (bsc#1268012).\n- CVE-2026-11824: heap-based buffer overflow vulnerability in the FTS5 full-text search extension that allows attackers\n  to cause a crash or execute arbitrary code (bsc#1268013).\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
